<h1>Webtext - FAQ</h1>
 
 <p><strong>Q. Why our new Webtext service is better then our last service?</strong><br />
  <strong>1.</strong> Your free 333 texts can be sent to international numbers; previously they could only be sent to Irish numbers.<br />
  <strong>2.</strong> Previously you could access Three Webtext service from Three website now there are a number of ways to access the 333 texts.</p>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&bull;</strong> Website<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&bull;</strong> iPhone App: available on Apple's App Store<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&bull;</strong> iPad App: available on Apple's App Store<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&bull;</strong> PC Client</p>
<p><strong>Q. What is webtext?</strong><br />
  <strong>A. </strong>Webtext, allows you to send texts free of charge from your mobile number via a number of platforms.<strong></strong></p>
<p><strong>Q. How many free Webtexts do I receive each month?</strong><br />
  A. 333 Webtexts each month provided that the text in each sms is 160 characters or less</p>
<p><strong>Q.How do I register for Webtext?</strong><br />
  A. To register for your free webtexts, simply key in your mobile number, email address, and click 'Register'. We'll send you a text message with a PIN number. When you've received the message, enter your mobile number and your PIN, click 'Login', and off you go! </p>
<p><strong>Q. How do I access the Three Webtext service?</strong><br />
  A. Three is offering its Webtext service in 4 different formats:<br /><br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&bull;</strong> Website  <br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&bull;</strong> iPhone App on the Apple App Store<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&bull;</strong> iPad App on the Apple App Store<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&bull;</strong> PC client <br /><br />
  You have to be a mobile or broadband customer of Three to avail of the Webtext service.</p>
<p><strong>Q. What are the key features of the Webtext Service?</strong><br /><br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&bull;</strong> Add contacts<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&bull;</strong> Import contacts from excel<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&bull;</strong> Add groups<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&bull;</strong> Schedule      SMS messages<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&bull;</strong> Get      replies direct to your mobile</p>

<p><strong>Q. Can I use all 4 Webtext services if I wish?</strong><br />
  A. Yes, as a Three customer, you can avail of the webtext service online, or via the PC client, the app store iPhone &amp; iPad app.</p>
<p><strong>Q. Do I need to register for each separate webtext service?</strong><br />
  A. No, your password and the pin is the same across all Webtext clients and apps.</p>
<p><strong>Q. Who can I send Webtext to?</strong><br />
  A. Webtext can be sent to all Irish mobile numbers and recently we've added International numbers to the service aswell.</p>
<p><strong>Q. How many Webtexts can I send to international numbers?</strong><br />
  A. All 333 Webtexts can be sent to international or Irish mobile numbers</p>
<p><strong>Q. Can I send a Webtext to a premium rate number or short code?</strong><br />
  A. No you can't use Webtexts to premium rate numbers or short codes</p>
<p><strong>Q. What is the total number of characters in a Webtext?</strong><br />
  A. Each message is 160 characters long using the standard GSM character set</p>
<p><strong>Q. What is the length of a message that can be sent by the Webtext service?</strong><br />
  A. A Webtext message can be up to 765 characters in length and where you exceed 160 characters multiple SMS messages are deducted from your monthly allowance. For example, if you send a message with 765 characters this will reduce your monthly allowance by 5 SMS. If you have used your monthly allowance the message will not be sent.</p>
<p><strong>Q What happens when I send 333 Webtexts in one month?</strong><br />
  A. The Webtext service allows you to send up to 333 free domestic or international SMS messages via webtext per calendar month.&nbsp; When you have used your month's allocation you have to wait until the next month for your next allocation of 333 free SMS.</p>
<p><strong>Q. Can I send more then 333 Webtexts in one month ?</strong><br />
  A. No, 333 is the total number of webtext which can be sent, per user in one calendar month.</p>
<p><strong>Q. Do I need to add the international code to the international phone number I'm sending the webtext to?</strong><br />
  A. Yes you need to ensure the international prefix is included in your contacts international mobile number.</p>
<p><strong>Q. Can I schedule Webtexts to be sent at specific times?</strong><br />
  A. Yes you can send your texts immediately or schedule them to be sent anytime within the next 7 days.&nbsp; The scheduling feature is only available on the Web and PC client versions of the Webtext service. </p>
<p><strong>Q. Can I set up a group to send Webtexts to?</strong><br />
  A. Yes it's easy to set up groups on the Web and PC Client versions of the Webtext service. Unfortunately, the group text service is not currently available on the iPAD or iPhone versions of the Webtext service.</p>
<p><strong>Q. &nbsp;</strong><strong>What is the max limit of contacts possible in a group for a standard user? </strong><br />
  A. 333 contacts as that's the maximum amount of texts you&nbsp;can send in one month&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Q. How many Webtexts can I send in one batch?</strong><br />
  A. You can send a maximum of 333&nbsp;messages in one batch as that's the total allocation&nbsp;of texts you&nbsp;can send in one month&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Q. Can I import my contacts from another file?</strong><br />
  Yes, we have now launched a new functionality on our online and PC client version of our Webtext service that allows our customers to import their contact from Excel into the Three webtext service. </p>

